Vandale de Oraculis p. 13.Boeotum in terrâ, craſſo
que ſub aere nati. "Born in a land of Dolts, and foggy Air.

But however Vandale himſelfe owns,Vandale p. 364. that theſe Verſes were diſperſt through all Grecia, Aſia, Africa, and other Regions, when Auguſtus made


his Collection; and where Virgil ſaw them is not greatly material here, but that he had ſeen Verſes which paſs'd for Cumaean Sibyl's, and wrote to one who is preſumed not to have been unacquainted with them, appears, when he ſays;

